<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="177" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="177">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="177">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guimaraes &amp; Ferreira-Jr" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Noteridae" genus="Notomicrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Notomicrus teramnus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="teramnus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="177">Notomicrus teramnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
would also appear a member of the 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Noteridae" genus="Notomicrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Notomicrus nanulus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nanulus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="177">Notomicrus nanulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, given the above-mentioned characters. An argument could be made that this is the case as it only appears to differ in the shape of the posterior lobes of the noterid platform being more angular than most species in the 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Noteridae" genus="Notomicrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Notomicrus nanulus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nanulus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="177">Notomicrus nanulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. This species otherwise appears to lack characters that would unite it with other species groups, though this will require examination and/or phylogenetic investigation. We abstain from placing it as member of the 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Noteridae" genus="Notomicrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Notomicrus nanulus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nanulus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="177">Notomicrus nanulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guimaraes &amp; Ferreira-Jr" authorityYear="2019" family="Noteridae" genus="N." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="N. teramnus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="177" rank="species" species="teramnus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="177">N. teramnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from a high elevation hygropetric habitat, which may present confounding morphological specialization. Aedeagal morphology is not here considered to be indicative of a particular placement, but the very unusual morphology of the aedeagus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guimaraes &amp; Ferreira-Jr" authorityYear="2019" family="Noteridae" genus="N." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="N. teramnus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="177" rank="species" species="teramnus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="177">N. teramnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4629.2.8" author="Guimaraes, BA" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="177" pagination="263 - 270" refId="B9" refString="Guimaraes, BA, Ferreira-Jr, N, 2019. Two new species and new records of Notomicrus Sharp, 1882 (Coleoptera: Noteridae) from Brazil. Zootaxa 4629 (2): 263 - 270, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4629.2.8" title="Two new species and new records of Notomicrus Sharp, 1882 (Coleoptera: Noteridae) from Brazil." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4629.2.8" volume="4629" year="2019">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Guimarães">Guimaraes</normalizedToken>
and Ferreira-Jr 2019
</bibRefCitation>
) further raises questions of placement.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
